cause 1) we are Catholic and wanted our children to be able to express their beliefs without ridicule and government restrictions and 2) private schools do not have to take everyone. Only people who are serious about their children's education and will take the time to invest in them will send their children to private schools. Before you think I am an elitist rich person, we had to scrape and borrow to get our kids through private schools. The proof that this worked for me is that 2 of my children have now graduated college with honors and our youngest is starting his junior year in college as an intern in Washington DC. Private schooling works! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="962" language="en" documentId="2987" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Mike out in the country" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:55PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="17" thumbsDown="0" origId="2987" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="962"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>